snippet.textDisplay:
(Reposting this comment so more people will see it and know the full truth)


Okay. Let's clear up some misinformation before the comment section becomes a total conspiracy theory wasteland, shall we?




1. As far as his accusers dying, the facts are as follows: The first accuser, the masseuse in CA, had been suffering from cancer prior to filing the suit. His family confirmed themselves that he died from cancer; KS had nothing to do with it. Now maybe you could argue that the stress from filing the lawsuit exacerbated his condition, but again, that has nothing to do with KS. The accuser made that choice to file the suit, so in a way, he died by his own hand.




The second accuser, Linda Louise Culkin, was a mentally deranged woman. She was obsessed with KS and sent him multiple threats to his life, as well as making bomb and anthrax threats to two of his workplaces. KS, understandably, was afraid for his life. It got so bad the FBI got involved and she was jailed. In her statement, she admitted she had mental health issues, so she's not exactly trustworthy. This is a proven fact; look up the case. She is not a victim, she is a criminal. Considering her struggles with mental health and how crazy she acted before, it wouldn't surprise me that she walked out into traffic without looking first. KS had nothing to do with her death either; she also died by her own hand.




2. As far as Epstein goes, there is no proof that KS knew him as anything more than an acquaintance. He took a trip on Epstein's plane ONCE, in 2002, with Bill Clinton and Chris Rock, on a humanitarian aid trip to Africa. This trip was well documented and there is no evidence that anything untoward happened. While it is a bit odd KS's info is in Epstein's black book, there is a simple explanation for that: Many of the people mentioned in the black book had only met Epstein briefly for financial meetings, or in some cases never met him at all. This is a FACT, look it up. Many of the "contacts" only knew him as a billionaire businessman, and if he had a plane available to go somewhere, why not use it? There's absolutely no evidence that KS knew Epstein as anything more than an acquaintance or that he knew anything about Epstein's illicit activities. You could make that argument for Bill Clinton, maybe, but not KS.




3. KS IS NOT A PEDOPHILE. END OF STORY. All of his accusers thus far have been young ADULT men at the time they were supposedly assaulted. A pedophile is only attracted to prepubescent children, according to the DSM. Also, considering the only case to make it to court, the Unruh case, was exposed as a money grab, I'm willing to bet many of these claims are either highly exaggerated or just plain lies to get money and publicity from him. If you look closely at many of them, many of the details just don't add up. The MeToo mass hysteria needs to end.




In conclusion, KS may be a creep, but he is not a pedophile nor a murderer. Next time you hear a conspiracy theory, think of Occam's Razor; the simplest explanation is usually the correct one. Stop seeing things that aren't there. Live your life; get off of 4Chan and Infowars, shut down your computer and go socialize a bit! Take off your tin foil hat and actually experience reality for once.
